sentences: Signe Lund-Skabo (15 April 1868 – 6 April 1950) was a Norwegian composer and music teacher.
Signe Lund was born in Christiania (now Oslo), Norway.
She was the daughter of Lieutenant Colonel Henrik Louis Bull Lund (1838–1891), and pianist Birgitte Theodora Carlsen (1843–1913), and was the sister of artist Henrik Lund (1879-1935).

Lund emigrated to the United States about 1900 and took a position teaching at Mayville State Normal School in Mayville, North Dakota.
She later worked in New York City and Chicago as a performer and lecturer until 1920.
